Oddly enough----I began to delete that word when I first wrote it, but then I left it, because I could find no other word to match the situation. But, for the politically-correct minded, here it is, revised:<br>
<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look less intellectually challenged if you read the log first, then post. (Note, I'm referring to *you* specifically, not to a population in general.)<br>
<br>
Or how about: <br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look less dimwitted if you read the log first, then post.<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look less feebleminded if you read the log first, then post.<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look less moronic if you read the log first, then post.<br>
<br>
Or, we could go with a more positive phrase:<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look more intelligent if you read the log first, then post.<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look smarter if you read the log first, then post.<br>
<br>
Tip2 for Jaranna: You look brighter if you read the log first, then post. <br>
<br>
But I'm not in a positive mood today, so I didn't opt for that route. Either way, my advice is sound: Read the post before commenting or don't post at all.<br>
<br>
Edit: added quote for reference<br>
Edit2: For those who truly were offended by my use of the word &quot;retarded,&quot; I do apologize, and I have since changed my post to be less offensive. Note that I did not mean to disrespect a population of individuals that others have inappropriately labeled &quot;retarded,&quot; but rather I was referring to Jaranna herself as a bit slow for responding so vehemently to a post without having read its contents.<br>
<br>
Also note that this is not an attack on the Circle of Sisters, whom I respect greatly for their gameplay and roleplay, nor is it an attack on Jaranna as a person, but rather it concerns the action of commenting on a post with such fervor without having read the contents of the original post. <br>
