<br>
President Clinton: Steals small items from the White House as he leaves office.  Certainly petty theft is not the philosophy of all Americans.  Cheats on his wife - certainly not a philosophy of all Americans either.<br>
<br>
Enron and WorldCom: One can hardly say doctoring the books or tampering with evidence is a philosophy for all Enron or WorldCom employees now.<br>
<br>
You get the idea.  Besides, she was defending one of her daughters to an outsider - perhaps she intended on addressing the issue internally.  I guess we'll never know.  Regardless, I agree it was not the most tactful way to do it, but to insult the entire guild was not appopriate either (perhaps less so than Vivienne's own response - though the train itself was likely uncalled for).<br>
