<br>
The way I handle this sort of thing is simple. The first time is coincidence; the second time is happenstance. The third time, of course, is enemy action. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I won't petition unless it's quite apparent that the action is intentional, and even then, I'll ask the person to stop first. Of course, as an Enchanter, I'm much more lenient towards trains, as I'm well-equipped to stop them. That, and I recognize that mistakes happen.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm glad the Sisters are handling this matter with the affected players. Hopefully, a solid understanding will come out of this and we can all go back to our regularly scheduled flaming of n00bs and uB3r guilds. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Illudin Arbitrator<br>
