<br>
A guild who unapologetically violates the Play Nice Policies by training guards onto others is everyone's business on this server.<br>
<br>
Aailin has not insulting you, nor your guild.  Your guild insulted itself.  He merely made your guild's reprehensible behavior public, and now you're embarrassed.<br>
<br>
I don't believe your apology is sincere.  Every time you tell us that Aailin did you wrong by making this public, you undercut the sincerity of that apology.  It begins to look more and more like your apology was insincere &quot;damage control.&quot;  Every time you qualify it, you undercut it.  Every &quot;but...&quot; on the end undercuts its credibility. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>
