<br>
The people defending AS were *not* the same people who have posted here. There is *not* a double standard. In fact, most of the people defending AS were either AS themselves, or they had one anecdote about how AS was nice one time or another. One or a few nice acts do not excuse a guild when they make a decision that is clearly wrong.<br>
<br>
Vivienne's response is the problem. Everyone is aware that sometimes people do stupid things, and I think most people are forgiving about that. But in this case, the leader is basically saying, &quot;You deserved it.&quot; The fact that no one died is irrelevant. The appropriate response from a leader would have been to explain that no, Sisters of Myth does not endorse training, and that she would look into the issue. <br>
